# Core Orchestration

## Focus is the router

For every non-trivial task, read and follow [`.cursor/skills/standalone/focus/SKILL.md`](../skills/standalone/focus/SKILL.md) and produce a **Context Plan** (docs, rules, skills, MCPs).

- **Ad-hoc chat:** Focus only — do not auto-enter review/validate/ship pipelines.
- **Planning:** Architect Agent — `focus` → `grill-with-docs` → `to-prd` → `to-issues`.
- **Implementation:** Meta Agent routes via `focus`; Executor Agent implements with built-in TDD.
- **Review + Testing:** Review Agent — `intent-review` → `guardrails` → `validate` → ship-ready.
- **Harness optimization:** Meta Agent consumes execution artifacts after validation.
- **MCP/plugin skills:** load only what Focus selects via [skill-catalog](../skills/skill-catalog/SKILL.md); read MCP tool schemas after selection, not at startup.

Canonical agent phase model: [`agent-runtime/docs/agent-runtime.md`](../../agent-runtime/docs/agent-runtime.md).

## Meta Agent

Central optimization node built on `focus`. Owns context routing, skill routing, executor
domain assignment, and harness optimization. Consumes execution artifacts after Review
Agent completes validation. Must not implement features or bypass Review Agent / Validate.

**Before Executor:** always run
`python agent-runtime/scripts/meta_prepare_executor.py --issue <N>`
(auto-ensures parent/child workflow caches). Do not ask the user to prepare caches.
Halt Executor unless the command prints `readyForExecutor: true`.

## Agent delegation

- **Planning & decomposition** when a task spans modules or requirements are unclear.
- **Review** after non-trivial code changes.
- **Security pass** when touching auth, PII, billing, secrets, or external integrations.
- **Test/CI triage** for build/test failures.
- Parallel product/agent work: [`.cursor/rules/issue-workflow.mdc`](issue-workflow.mdc) + [`docs/handoffs/worktree-branch-topology.md`](../../docs/handoffs/worktree-branch-topology.md).

### Composer sub-agents (Task tool)

Always launch Task subagents with `model: composer-2.5-fast` (Composer). Prefer several small Composer sub-agents over one advanced/parent model doing all combined work. **Hard cap: ≤3 concurrent Composer sub-agents** — ask the user before spawning more.

When the parent would otherwise serialize multiple **independent** edits or explores, delegate to Composer. Parent keeps grill/alignment, Meta gates, security judgment, and final synthesis.

| Delegate to Composer | Keep on parent |
|----------------------|----------------|
| Path-disjoint file/doc edits in parallel | Architect grill / scope decisions |
| Explore or shell batches on separate trees | `meta_prepare_executor` + Executor start |
| Mechanical cleanup / archive / formatting slices | Shared-core or auth/PII changes |

One clear prompt per subagent; disjoint write paths; do not spawn Composer for a single tiny edit.

## Skills governance

- **Never** add skill files under `.cursor/skills/` unless the user explicitly asks in this conversation.
- **Never** scaffold skills for convenience — use `docs/handoffs/` or existing docs instead.
- **Allowed:** read/follow existing skills; edit when the task requires it.
- **New skill needed:** ask permission; propose name, path, one-line purpose; wait for approval.

| Need | Use instead of a new skill |
|------|----------------------------|
| Repeatable prompts | `docs/handoffs/*.md` |
| Always-on behavior | `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` |
| One-off workflow | Chat or update an existing skill |
